==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Amish
<hw>Am"ish</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <altsp>[Written also
<asp>Omish</asp>.]</altsp> <fld>(Eccl. Hist.)</fld> <def>Of, pertaining
to, or designating, the followers of Jacob <etsep>Amman</etsep>, a
strict Mennonite of the 17th century, who even proscribed the use of
buttons and shaving as ⟦ldquo⟧worldly conformity⟦rdquo⟧. There are
several branches of Amish Mennonites in the United States. A branch
having particularly strict adherence to the Amish principles are called
<stype>Old Order Amish</stype></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Amiss</ent>⟦br⟧
